Corona Virus Precautions

3/12/20

Pursuant to directives from Governor Brown, the State of Oregon is issuing the following guidance, with the primary goal of slowing transmission of the coronavirus in Oregon:

All large gatherings over 250 people are canceled statewide, effectively immediately, for four weeks (through April 8, 2020).
All other events are to be canceled or recommended to be modified as follows:

Make events virtual when possible;
Make performances and content available online;
Change the location of event to an outdoor setting;
Transition a large event to multiple events with fewer people.

